Review saved. Here's the summary:

**6 findings** in `nsqd/nsqd.go`:

| # | Type | Severity | Description |
|---|------|----------|-------------|
| 1 | BUG | Medium | Line 121–122: `TLSClientAuthPolicy != ""` unconditionally overwrites `TLSRequired`, clobbering explicit user setting of `TLSRequiredExceptHTTP` |
| 2 | BUG | **High** | Lines 370–398: `Exit()` closes listeners but never closes active TCP connections. `tcpServer` has no conn tracking. Unsubscribed clients (stateInit/stateConnected) and their IOLoop goroutines are never cleaned up. |
| 3 | BUG | Medium | Line 315: `PersistMetadata()` is exported but iterates `topicMap` without holding a lock internally — relies on caller discipline with no enforcement |
| 4 | QUESTION | Low | Lines 541–548 + 121–122: Invalid `TLSClientAuthPolicy` (typo) silently defaults to `NoClientCert` while simultaneously escalating `TLSRequired` — dangerous combination |
| 5 | QUESTION | Low | Line 535: Dead initialization of `VerifyClientCertIfGiven` immediately overwritten by switch |
| 6 | QUESTION | Low | Lines 461–479: `DeleteExistingTopic` TOCTOU gap between RLock check and Lock delete |

**Assessment: FIX FIRST** — Finding #2 is the most impactful (shutdown can't guarantee clean exit for unsubscribed clients).
